nodes.title: SpaceX
nodes.desc: A private aerospace manufacturer and space transport services company founded in 2002 by Elon Musk. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/)

nodes.title: Reusable Rockets
nodes.desc: A type of rocket that can be launched into space multiple times, significantly reducing the cost of access to space. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/reusability/)

nodes.title: NASA Commercial Crew Program
nodes.desc: A program established by NASA to develop private spacecraft capable of carrying astronauts to the International Space Station. [More Info](https://www.nasa.gov/commercialcrew)

nodes.title: NASA Artemis Program
nodes.desc: A program established by NASA to return humans to the lunar surface by 2024 and establish a sustainable presence on the Moon. [More Info](https://www.nasa.gov/artemis)

nodes.title: SpaceX Raptor Engine
nodes.desc: A full-flow staged combustion cycle engine developed by SpaceX, designed to power the Starship spacecraft. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/raptor/)

nodes.title: SpaceX Merlin Engine
nodes.desc: A family of rocket engines developed by SpaceX, used to power the Falcon 9 and Falcon Heavy launch vehicles. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/merlin/)

nodes.title: Grid Fins
nodes.desc: A type of control surface used by SpaceX to steer its rockets during re-entry and landing. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/grid-fins/)

nodes.title: Autonomous Spaceport Drone Ship
nodes.desc: A type of drone ship used by SpaceX to recover its rockets at sea. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/asds/)

nodes.title: Falcon 9
nodes.desc: A reusable launch vehicle developed by SpaceX, designed to transport satellites, spacecraft, and humans to orbit. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/falcon9/)

nodes.title: Falcon Heavy
nodes.desc: A heavy-lift launch vehicle developed by SpaceX, designed to transport large payloads to orbit and beyond. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/falconheavy/)

nodes.title: Dragon
nodes.desc: A reusable spacecraft developed by SpaceX, designed to transport cargo and crew to the International Space Station. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/dragon/)

nodes.title: Starship
nodes.desc: A next-generation reusable spacecraft developed by SpaceX, designed to take humans to the Moon, Mars, and other destinations in the solar system. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/starship/)

nodes.title: Mars Colonization
nodes.desc: A long-term goal of SpaceX to establish a permanent, self-sustaining human presence on Mars. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/mars/)

nodes.title: Lunar Missions
nodes.desc: A series of missions planned by SpaceX to send private citizens to the Moon. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/lunar/)

nodes.title: SpaceX Launch Facilities
nodes.desc: A network of launch sites and facilities used by SpaceX to launch its rockets, including Cape Canaveral, Vandenberg, and Boca Chica. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/launch-sites/)

nodes.title: SpaceX Test Facilities
nodes.desc: A network of test sites and facilities used by SpaceX to test its rockets and spacecraft, including McGregor and Hawthorne. [More Info](https://www.spacex.com/test-sites/)
